When docker gets installed, the file system gets generated in this structure:
/var/lib/docker, under this folder there are 4 folders:
aufs
containers
image
volumes


When a container is destroyed, we probably want to store the data, data persistence is the process of storing data on non-volatile storage (like hard drives, SSDs, 
or databases) so it survives system reboots, power outages, or application termination.
To keep the data in the container, we can add a persistent volume to the container.
